    // ── ARTICLE: Entrevue parrainage époux ──────────────────────────────────
    'art.entrevue.page.title':  'Spousal sponsorship interview: what to expect (with sample questions) | MDPL Immigration',
    'art.entrevue.bc.current':  'Family Sponsorship',
    'art.entrevue.cat1':        'Family Sponsorship',
    'art.entrevue.cat2':        'IRCC Interview',
    'art.entrevue.hero.title':  'Spousal sponsorship interview:<br /><em>what to expect (with sample questions)</em>',
    'art.entrevue.hero.lead':   'As part of a spousal or conjugal sponsorship application, IRCC may invite the couple to an interview. The purpose: to verify that your relationship is genuine and in good faith, and not an arrangement for immigration purposes. This is not systematic — an interview is generally requested when the officer needs clarification or has doubts.',
    'art.entrevue.h2.1':        'What to expect <em>at the interview</em>',
    'art.entrevue.li1':         'The interview may take place <strong>in person</strong> (at an immigration office or visa application centre), or sometimes by <strong>telephone or video conference</strong>.',
    'art.entrevue.li2':         'The couple may be <strong>interviewed separately</strong>, with their answers compared afterward to check for consistency.',
    'art.entrevue.li3':         'Bring: your <strong>passport</strong>, the <strong>convocation letter</strong>, and your <strong>proof of relationship</strong> (photos, communications, proof of cohabitation, joint finances, etc.).',
    'art.entrevue.li4':         'The officer is primarily assessing the <strong>consistency and naturalness of your answers</strong>. Be honest — inconsistencies raise suspicions.',
    'art.entrevue.li5':         'It is normal to be nervous; the officer knows this.',
    'art.entrevue.pullquote':   'The officer is not trying to trap you. They are trying to confirm that your relationship is real. Consistency and honesty are your best assets.',
    'art.entrevue.h2.2':        'Sample questions <em>(for reference)</em>',
    'art.entrevue.p1':          'Questions asked during a sponsorship interview cover three main themes: your history together, your daily life, and your plans for the future. The following are representative examples, provided for reference only.',
    'art.entrevue.h3.1':        'Your meeting and your story',
    'art.entrevue.q1':          'How and where did you meet? When?',
    'art.entrevue.q2':          'When did your relationship begin? When did you get married?',
    'art.entrevue.q3':          'Tell me about your first meeting, your marriage proposal, your wedding (date, location, guests).',
    'art.entrevue.h3.2':        'Your daily life',
    'art.entrevue.q4':          'What does your spouse do for work? What are their hobbies?',
    'art.entrevue.q5':          'Describe your home. Who takes care of what around the house?',
    'art.entrevue.q6':          'What did you do together last weekend?',
    'art.entrevue.q7':          'What is your spouse\'s favourite dish?',
    'art.entrevue.h3.3':        'Your family and your future',
    'art.entrevue.q8':          'Tell me about your spouse\'s family (names, relationships).',
    'art.entrevue.q9':          'Do you have children? Are you planning to have children?',
    'art.entrevue.q10':         'What are your plans for the future together?',
    'art.entrevue.alert.title': 'Inconsistent answers are taken seriously',
    'art.entrevue.alert.p':     'When both partners are interviewed separately, their answers are compared. Significant discrepancies on concrete facts (dates, places, events) may raise doubts about the authenticity of the relationship. Make sure both partners are well acquainted with the important facts.',
    'art.entrevue.h2.3':        'How to <em>prepare</em>',
    'art.entrevue.prep1':       'Review your own application before the interview.',
    'art.entrevue.prep2':       'Do not memorize answers "by heart" — be natural and honest.',
    'art.entrevue.prep3':       'Make sure both partners are well acquainted with the important facts (dates, events).',
    'art.entrevue.prep4':       'Prepare and bring your documents (passport, convocation letter, proof of relationship).',
    'art.entrevue.cta.h3':      'Did you receive a convocation? <em>Prepare with a professional.</em>',
    'art.entrevue.cta.p':       'A sponsorship interview can feel stressful, but good preparation makes a real difference. At MDPL Immigration, we support couples in preparing their file and their interview.',
    'art.entrevue.cta.btn1':    'Book an appointment',
    'art.entrevue.cta.btn2':    'Contact us',
    'art.entrevue.note.title':  'MDPL Immigration — Immigration Consulting Firm',
    'art.entrevue.note.p':      'The information in this article is provided for general and informational purposes only. The sample questions are indicative and IRCC practices may vary. Each file is unique. If you have doubts about your situation, contact MDPL Immigration for a personalized assessment.',
    'art.entrevue.related.h2':  'Related articles',
    'art.entrevue.rel1.tag':    'Family Sponsorship',
    'art.entrevue.rel1.title':  'He lives in Ontario, works in Quebec: a sponsorship file that almost went off the rails',
    'art.entrevue.rel2.tag':    'Common Mistakes',
    'art.entrevue.rel2.title':  'The 6 most common errors in an immigration application (and how to avoid them)',
    'art.entrevue.rel3.tag':    'Blog',
    'art.entrevue.rel3.title':  'View all articles on the MDPL Immigration blog',

