    // ── article-depute-aide-dossier-immigration.html ──
    'art.depute.page.title':    'How a Member of Parliament can help with your immigration file — and what they can\'t do | MDPL Immigration',
    'art.depute.bc.current':    'Canadian Immigration',
    'art.depute.cat1':          'Canadian Immigration',
    'art.depute.cat2':          'IRCC • Member of Parliament',
    'art.depute.hero.title':    'How a Member of Parliament can help with your immigration file — <em>and what they can\'t do</em>',
    'art.depute.hero.lead':     'When an immigration file is delayed or seems stuck, many wonder whether their MP can intervene. A federal Member of Parliament can take steps with IRCC on your behalf, but their role has important limits to know.',
    'art.depute.h2.1':          'What an MP <em>CAN do</em>',
    'art.depute.li1':           'Submit an <strong>information or status request</strong> about your file to IRCC on your behalf. You will generally need to live in their constituency.',
    'art.depute.li2':           '<strong>Flag an abnormal processing delay</strong> or an urgent or humanitarian situation, and draw IRCC\'s attention to your file.',
    'art.depute.li3':           '<strong>Request an explanation</strong> for a delay or the current status of a file.',
    'art.depute.li4':           'Their office often has <strong>staff dedicated to constituent casework</strong>, who communicate directly with IRCC on your behalf.',
    'art.depute.pullquote':     'An MP can open a door, draw attention to an unusual delay, or flag an urgent situation — they cannot decide in place of IRCC.',
    'art.depute.h2.2':          'What an MP <em>CANNOT do</em>',
    'art.depute.li5':           '<strong>Approve, deny, or influence the decision</strong> on your file: the IRCC officer remains solely responsible for the outcome.',
    'art.depute.li6':           '<strong>Speed up or guarantee faster processing</strong>, or move you ahead of other applicants.',
    'art.depute.li7':           '<strong>Provide legal immigration advice</strong> or represent you: that is the role of an authorized representative — a regulated consultant (RCIC) or a lawyer.',
    'art.depute.li8':           '<strong>Intervene for someone outside their constituency</strong>: their mandate is limited to residents of their own electoral district.',
    'art.depute.alert.title':   'Do not confuse an MP\'s inquiry with professional representation',
    'art.depute.alert.p':       'An MP can ask questions of IRCC, but cannot analyze your file, assess your legal options, prepare an application, or represent you. For a strategy tailored to your situation, a regulated consultant or immigration lawyer is the right professional.',
    'art.depute.h2.3':          'Key <em>takeaways</em>',
    'art.depute.li9':           'You will normally need to <strong>sign a consent form</strong> so the MP\'s office can inquire with IRCC on your behalf.',
    'art.depute.li10':          'Immigration is a <strong>federal</strong> jurisdiction: it is your <strong>federal MP</strong> who can intervene with IRCC.',
    'art.depute.li11':          '<strong>In Quebec</strong>, for matters relating to provincial selection — the CSQ or MIFI — it is a <strong>provincial elected official</strong> (Member of the National Assembly) who can intervene with MIFI.',
    'art.depute.li12':          'An MP is a <strong>complement</strong> to, not a substitute for, professional immigration support.',
    'art.depute.cta.h3':        'Is your file stuck or delayed? <em>Let\'s review it together.</em>',
    'art.depute.cta.p':         'An MP\'s follow-up can complement your approach, but it does not replace a professional review of your file. At MDPL Immigration, we assess your situation, identify blockers, and guide you toward the right solutions.',
    'art.depute.cta.btn1':      'Book a consultation',
    'art.depute.cta.btn2':      'Contact us',
    'art.depute.note.title':    'MDPL Immigration — Immigration consulting firm',
    'art.depute.note.p':        'The information in this article is provided for general informational purposes only. Procedures and practices are subject to change. Each case is unique. If you have questions about your situation, contact MDPL Immigration for a personalized assessment.',
    'art.depute.related.h2':    'Related articles',
    'art.depute.rel1.tag':      'Canadian Immigration',
    'art.depute.rel1.title':    'What is an ATIP request and when to file one (especially after a refusal)',
    'art.depute.rel2.tag':      'Documents',
    'art.depute.rel2.title':    'The importance of submitting your documents on time in Canadian immigration',
    'art.depute.rel3.tag':      'Blog',
    'art.depute.rel3.title':    'See all articles on the MDPL Immigration blog',

    // ── blog card art19 ──
    'blog.art19.tag':     'Canadian Immigration',
    'blog.art19.title':   'How a Member of Parliament can help with your immigration file — and what they can\'t do',
    'blog.art19.excerpt': 'A federal MP can make inquiries to IRCC about a delayed or stalled file — but their role has important limits to know. What they can do, and what they cannot.',
    'blog.art19.kw1':     'Member of Parliament immigration',
    'blog.art19.kw2':     'MP help immigration case',
    'blog.art19.kw3':     'IRCC processing delay',

    // ── article-biometrie-portail-vfs.html ──
    'art.bio.page.title':    'Biometrics: what to do when VFS does not respond — the portal option | MDPL Immigration',
    'art.bio.bc.current':    'Canadian Immigration',
    'art.bio.cat1':          'Canadian Immigration',
    'art.bio.cat2':          'Biometrics • VFS',
    'art.bio.hero.title':    'Biometrics: what to do when VFS does not respond — <em>the portal option</em>',
    'art.bio.hero.lead':     'If VFS Global does not respond by phone or email to schedule your biometrics appointment, the VFS portal is the solution. Here are the steps to follow and the critical points not to miss.',
    'art.bio.h2.1':          'How to use the VFS portal to schedule your <em>biometrics appointment</em>',
    'art.bio.p.intro':       'When VFS Global does not respond by phone or email, the online portal is the recommended solution. Follow these steps in order:',
    'art.bio.s1.title':      'Download your biometrics letter (summons)',
    'art.bio.s1.text':       'In the portal, first download your biometrics letter — the summons sent by IRCC. Save it to your computer.',
    'art.bio.s1.warn':       'DO NOT rename the document as downloaded. The original file name is required for the portal to recognize your file.',
    'art.bio.s2.title':      'Upload the letter to the portal',
    'art.bio.s2.text':       'Upload the letter into the portal. Your information (full name and file number) will fill in automatically from the document.',
    'art.bio.s3.title':      'Add the missing information',
    'art.bio.s3.text':       'Complete the remaining fields: your email address and phone number.',
    'art.bio.s3.warn':       'IMPORTANT — Phone number: no dashes, no spaces. Enter only the digits run together (e.g., 5141234567). An incorrect format may block your request.',
    'art.bio.s4.title':      'Provide three available dates',
    'art.bio.s4.text':       'Propose three dates on which you are available for your biometrics appointment. Choose realistic and varied dates to make scheduling easier.',
    'art.bio.s5.title':      'Confirmation email',
    'art.bio.s5.text':       'You will receive a confirmation email from VFS within a maximum of 2 hours. In practice, the reply often arrives sooner.',
    'art.bio.s5.info':       'Check your spam folder if you receive nothing within 2 hours.',
    'art.bio.h2.2':          'What to bring <em>on the day of your appointment</em>',
    'art.bio.bring.p':       'On the day of your VFS appointment, you must bring the following two documents:',
    'art.bio.li1':           '<strong>The biometrics request (summons) — 9-page document</strong>: this is the official document received from IRCC asking you to provide your biometric data.',
    'art.bio.li2':           '<strong>Your valid passport</strong>: original identification required for fingerprinting and photo.',
    'art.bio.alert.title':   'Warning — both documents are mandatory',
    'art.bio.alert.p':       'Without the 9-page document AND your passport, you will be turned away and will need to rebook an appointment. Do not show up without both documents.',
    'art.bio.cta.h3':        'A file in progress, questions about next steps? <em>We can guide you.</em>',
    'art.bio.cta.p':         'Biometrics are part of a larger process. At MDPL Immigration, we accompany each step of your file to avoid mistakes and delays.',
    'art.bio.cta.btn1':      'Book a consultation',
    'art.bio.cta.btn2':      'Contact us',
    'art.bio.note.title':    'MDPL Immigration — Immigration consulting firm',
    'art.bio.note.p':        'The information in this article is provided for general informational purposes only. VFS and IRCC procedures are subject to change. If you have questions about your situation, contact MDPL Immigration for a personalized assessment.',
    'art.bio.related.h2':    'Related articles',
    'art.bio.rel1.tag':      'Canadian Immigration',
    'art.bio.rel1.title':    'What is an ATIP request and when to file one (especially after a refusal)',
    'art.bio.rel2.tag':      'Documents',
    'art.bio.rel2.title':    'The importance of submitting your documents on time in Canadian immigration',
    'art.bio.rel3.tag':      'Blog',
    'art.bio.rel3.title':    'See all articles on the MDPL Immigration blog',

    // ── blog card art20 ──
    'blog.art20.tag':     'Canadian Immigration',
    'blog.art20.title':   'Biometrics: what to do when VFS does not respond — the portal option',
    'blog.art20.excerpt': 'VFS Global not responding? Use the VFS portal to schedule your biometrics appointment. Step-by-step guide and what to bring on the day.',
    'blog.art20.kw1':     'biometrics VFS',
    'blog.art20.kw2':     'VFS portal appointment',
    'blog.art20.kw3':     'IRCC biometrics',

    // ── article-suivi-demande-recu-paiement.html ──
    'art.suivi.page.title':    'Confirm receipt of your application and track your file using the payment receipt number | MDPL Immigration',
    'art.suivi.bc.current':    'Canadian Immigration',
    'art.suivi.cat1':          'Canadian Immigration',
    'art.suivi.cat2':          'IRCC • File tracking',
    'art.suivi.hero.title':    'Confirm receipt of your application and find your file using the <em>payment receipt number</em>',
    'art.suivi.hero.lead':     'You sent your immigration application by registered mail and have not heard from IRCC? Here is how to confirm your application is in processing and how to get your file number.',
    'art.suivi.h2.1':          'Steps to confirm receipt and <em>track your application</em>',
    'art.suivi.p.intro':       'These steps apply to applications sent by registered mail — work permits, study permits, temporary residence, and other paper applications submitted to IRCC.',
    'art.suivi.s1.title':      'Keep a complete record of your application',
    'art.suivi.s1.text':       'Before sending anything, keep a copy of your entire application and note in a log: the date of mailing, the contents, and the postal tracking number.',
    'art.suivi.s2.title':      'Send by registered mail',
    'art.suivi.s2.text':       'Sending by registered mail generates a tracking number. This postal tracking confirms delivery of your application to IRCC — it is your first proof of receipt.',
    'art.suivi.s3.title':      'No acknowledgment of receipt from IRCC is normal',
    'art.suivi.s3.text':       'With a registered mail submission, you often do not receive a formal acknowledgment of receipt from IRCC — sometimes an email, sometimes nothing.',
    'art.suivi.s3.warn':       'No acknowledgment of receipt does not mean your file is not in processing. This is normal for paper applications.',
    'art.suivi.s4.title':      'You need your file number to use the IRCC webform',
    'art.suivi.s4.text':       'To follow up via the IRCC webform or for any official communication, you will need your file number (UCI number or application number). Here is how to get it.',
    'art.suivi.s5.title':      'Get your file number using the payment receipt number',
    'art.suivi.s5.text':       'Call Immigration Canada (IRCC) and provide your <strong>payment receipt number</strong> (the receipt for the application fees paid when you submitted). This is one of the simplest ways to locate your file in their system.',
    'art.suivi.s5.info':       'Keep your payment receipt from day one — it is a key document for any follow-up.',
    'art.suivi.s6.title':      'Identity verification by the IRCC officer',
    'art.suivi.s6.text':       'The officer will ask identity verification questions before sharing any information about your file. It is the payment receipt number that allows them to locate your application in their system.',
    'art.suivi.s7.title':      'The final decision usually arrives by email',
    'art.suivi.s7.text':       'Once your application has been processed, the final decision (approval or refusal) is generally communicated by email. Make sure your email address is correct and check your spam folder as well.',
    'art.suivi.info.title':    'About the IRCC webform',
    'art.suivi.info.p':        'The IRCC webform is the official online tool for submitting an inquiry about your file. To use it, you will need your file number or UCI number. If you do not have them yet, use the phone call first (step 5) to obtain them.',
    'art.suivi.cta.h3':        'No news from your file for several months? <em>Let\'s see what can be done.</em>',
    'art.suivi.cta.p':         'Proactive follow-up is essential to prevent your file from stalling without reason. At MDPL Immigration, we know the official channels and the steps to take to move your file forward.',
    'art.suivi.cta.btn1':      'Book a consultation',
    'art.suivi.cta.btn2':      'Contact us',
    'art.suivi.note.title':    'MDPL Immigration — Immigration consulting firm',
    'art.suivi.note.p':        'The information in this article is provided for general informational purposes only. IRCC procedures are subject to change. If you have questions about your situation, contact MDPL Immigration for a personalized assessment.',
    'art.suivi.related.h2':    'Related articles',
    'art.suivi.rel1.tag':      'Canadian Immigration',
    'art.suivi.rel1.title':    'How a Member of Parliament can help with your immigration file — and what they can\'t do',
    'art.suivi.rel2.tag':      'Canadian Immigration',
    'art.suivi.rel2.title':    'What is an ATIP request and when to file one (especially after a refusal)',
    'art.suivi.rel3.tag':      'Blog',
    'art.suivi.rel3.title':    'See all articles on the MDPL Immigration blog',

    // ── blog card art21 ──
    'blog.art21.tag':     'Canadian Immigration',
    'blog.art21.title':   'Confirm receipt of your application and track your file using the payment receipt number',
    'blog.art21.excerpt': 'No acknowledgment of receipt from IRCC? That\'s normal for registered mail. Here\'s how to confirm your application is in processing and get your IRCC file number.',
    'blog.art21.kw1':     'IRCC application tracking',
    'blog.art21.kw2':     'payment receipt number',
    'blog.art21.kw3':     'IRCC file number',

    // ── article-etudier-canada-permis-etudes-exemptions.html ──
    'art.etudes.page.title':        'Who can study in Canada with or without a study permit? Rules, exemptions and special cases | MDPL Immigration',
    'art.etudes.bc.current':        'Canadian Immigration',
    'art.etudes.cat1':              'Canadian Immigration',
    'art.etudes.cat2':              'Study Permit • IRCC',
    'art.etudes.hero.title':        'Who can study in Canada <em>with or without a study permit?</em>',
    'art.etudes.hero.lead':         'The answer depends on your status in Canada, the length of the program, and your specific situation. Complete guide: general rule, short-term exemption, temporary policy for work permit holders, asylum claimants, and minor children — with a summary table and legal references.',
    'art.etudes.h2.1':              'The general rule',
    'art.etudes.p1':                'A study permit is required for any program of <strong>more than 6 months</strong> offered by a <strong>designated learning institution (DLI)</strong>. This includes not only university and college programs, but also <strong>vocational and technical training</strong> — any structured program delivered by a DLI that exceeds 6 months in duration. The conditions for issuance of a study permit are set out in section 216 IRPR.',
    'art.etudes.h2.2':              'The short-term studies exemption (6 months or less) — <em>s. 188 IRPR</em>',
    'art.etudes.s2.p1':             'Any person with <strong>valid status</strong> in Canada may follow a program of <strong>6 months or less without a study permit</strong>, provided the program is completed before the end of their authorized period of stay.',
    'art.etudes.s2.who.title':      'Who can use this exemption',
    'art.etudes.s2.li1':            'Visitors (with valid status — visitor visa, eTA, or visitor record)',
    'art.etudes.s2.li2':            'Work permit holders with valid status',
    'art.etudes.s2.li3':            'Any other temporary resident with valid status in Canada',
    'art.etudes.pullquote':         'Essential condition: the program must be <strong>completed before your authorized period of stay expires</strong>. If your status expires before the end of the course, the exemption does not apply.',
    'art.etudes.h2.3':              'Temporary policy for work permit holders — <em>s. 25.2 IRPA</em>',
    'art.etudes.alert.title':       'Warning — expires June 27, 2026. No extension announced.',
    'art.etudes.alert.p1':          'This public interest policy ends on <strong>June 27, 2026</strong>. No extension has been announced by IRCC as of the publication date of this article (June 2026).',
    'art.etudes.alert.p2':          'After that date, work permit holders who do not qualify under the general exemption may only study without a study permit for programs of <strong>6 months or less</strong>. Studying beyond 6 months without a study permit will be unauthorized.',
    'art.etudes.s3.p1':             'This public interest policy, issued under section 25.2 IRPA, allows certain work permit holders to study in Canada without a study permit, <strong>regardless of program length</strong>, during the policy\'s validity period.',
    'art.etudes.s3.crit.title':     'Eligibility requirements',
    'art.etudes.s3.crit.li1':       'Your <strong>initial</strong> work permit application was <strong>received by IRCC on or before June 7, 2023</strong>, OR',
    'art.etudes.s3.crit.li2':       'You <strong>renewed</strong> your work permit under section 201 IRPR, that renewal application was received on or before June 7, 2023, and you are authorized to work under section 186(u) IRPR.',
    'art.etudes.s3.period.title':   'Policy validity period',
    'art.etudes.s3.period.p':       'June 27, 2023 to <strong>June 27, 2026</strong>.',
    'art.etudes.s3.ret.title':      'Key points',
    'art.etudes.s3.ret.li1':        'No extension of this policy has been announced as of this date.',
    'art.etudes.s3.ret.li2':        'After June 27, 2026, the <strong>general rule resumes</strong>: programs of 6 months or less only, without a study permit.',
    'art.etudes.s3.ret.li3':        'Studies completed without a study permit <strong>do not count toward the PGWP</strong> (Post-Graduation Work Permit).',
    'art.etudes.s3.ret.li4':        'Studying without authorization after the expiry date may <strong>jeopardize your status</strong> in Canada.',
    'art.etudes.h2.4':              'Asylum claimants — <em>a special and counter-intuitive case</em>',
    'art.etudes.s4.p1':             'Most asylum claimants do <strong>not have temporary resident status</strong> or a formal authorized period of stay. The 6-month exemption (s. 188 IRPR) is therefore generally <strong>not available</strong> to them.',
    'art.etudes.s4.p2':             'As a result, <strong>a study permit is required even for a short course</strong>.',
    'art.etudes.s4.info.title':     'Good news',
    'art.etudes.s4.info.p':         'Asylum claimants may apply for a study permit <strong>from within Canada</strong>, under section 215 IRPR, without having to leave the country. They are also <strong>exempt from the biometrics requirement</strong> for this specific application.',
    'art.etudes.s4.cas.title':      'Two situations to distinguish',
    'art.etudes.s4.cas.a':          '<strong>(a) Asylum claimant WITHOUT temporary resident status</strong> → study permit required, even for a short program (s. 215 IRPR).',
    'art.etudes.s4.cas.b':          '<strong>(b) Asylum claimant who held valid temporary resident status</strong> at the time of filing their asylum claim → may use the 6-month exemption (s. 188 IRPR) if all conditions are met.',
    'art.etudes.s4.note.p':         'Note: certain work permits issued to asylum claimants carry the notation <em>"does not confer temporary resident status (s. 202 IRPR)."</em> This type of permit <strong>does not authorize studying without a study permit</strong>.',
    'art.etudes.h2.5':              'Minor children — <em>s. 30(2) IRPA</em>',
    'art.etudes.s5.p':              'Under section 30(2) of IRPA, minor children may attend <strong>kindergarten, elementary school, and secondary school</strong> in Canada <strong>without a study permit</strong>, regardless of their immigration situation.',
    'art.etudes.h2.6':              'Summary table',
    'art.etudes.tbl.h1':            'Situation',
    'art.etudes.tbl.h2':            'Study permit required?',
    'art.etudes.tbl.h3':            'Legal basis',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r1.s':          'Program of more than 6 months at a DLI',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r1.p':          'Yes',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r1.l':          'IRPA + s. 216 IRPR',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r2.s':          'Program of 6 months or less, valid status, completed before end of authorized stay',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r2.p':          'No',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r2.l':          'S. 188 IRPR',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r3.s':          'Work permit holder (application received on or before June 7, 2023) — before June 27, 2026',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r3.p':          'No (regardless of program length)',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r3.l':          'S. 25.2 IRPA',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r4.s':          'Asylum claimant without temporary resident status',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r4.p':          'Yes (even for a short course)',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r4.l':          'S. 215 IRPR (application from within Canada)',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r5.s':          'Asylum claimant with valid TR status at the time of filing',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r5.p':          'No (if program ≤ 6 months)',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r5.l':          'S. 188 IRPR',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r6.s':          'Minor child (kindergarten, elementary, or secondary school)',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r6.p':          'No',
    'art.etudes.tbl.r6.l':          'S. 30(2) IRPA',
    'art.etudes.cta.h3':            'Is your situation complex? <em>Let\'s review it together.</em>',
    'art.etudes.cta.p':             'Whether you need a study permit, an exemption applies to your case, you are an asylum claimant wanting to study in Canada, or a policy is about to expire — the rules are precise and the consequences of an error can be lasting. MDPL Immigration will clarify your situation and guide you toward the right steps.',
    'art.etudes.cta.btn1':          'Book a consultation',
    'art.etudes.cta.btn2':          'Contact us',
    'art.etudes.note.title':        'MDPL Immigration — Immigration consulting firm',
    'art.etudes.note.p':            'The information in this article is provided for general informational purposes only, based on IRCC policies and Canadian immigration law as of June 2026. Rules and procedures are subject to change. Each case is unique. This content does not replace personalized advice from a Regulated Canadian Immigration Consultant (RCIC) or a lawyer.',
    'art.etudes.related.h2':        'Related articles and services',
    'art.etudes.rel1.tag':          'MDPL Services',
